A round of applause for Ms. Sky, please.

271
00:16:45,080 --> 00:16:46,840
Dancing is a physics equation.

272
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,400
Every movement of the crew

273
00:16:48,400 --> 00:16:50,400
can be converted into kinetic energy.

274
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:53,000
The first step, apply 7.5 N of force.

275
00:16:53,000 --> 00:16:54,840
The second step, maintain velocity.

276
00:16:54,840 --> 00:16:56,640
The third step, momentum.

277
00:16:56,640 --> 00:17:00,080
And the fourth step, maintain acceleration.

278
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:02,560
Great theory, poor execution.

279
00:17:06,920 --> 00:17:09,200
No matter how much time passes,

280
00:17:09,200 --> 00:17:12,000
the soul of All-New San...

281
00:17:12,000 --> 00:17:16,000
can only synchronize with your body at 15%, it seems.

282
00:17:17,000 --> 00:17:20,320
Wait, you two know each other?

283
00:17:20,320 --> 00:17:21,320
That’s right.

284
00:17:28,400 --> 00:17:31,080
It’s been a long time,

285
00:17:31,080 --> 00:17:32,680
New.

286
00:17:32,680 --> 00:17:36,120
So you’ve finally revealed your true self,

287
00:17:36,120 --> 00:17:37,760
O-Liang.

288
00:17:37,760 --> 00:17:39,120
Huh?

289
00:17:39,120 --> 00:17:40,920
O-Liang?

290
00:17:40,920 --> 00:17:42,640
O-Liang...

291
00:17:42,640 --> 00:17:45,320
O-Liang and I have been rivals forever.

292
00:17:45,320 --> 00:17:48,280
In Mathematics, I won.

293
00:17:48,280 --> 00:17:51,080
I left you in the dust!

294
00:17:53,000 --> 00:17:54,400
But...

295
00:17:55,600 --> 00:17:57,040
but I had to lose

296
00:17:57,040 --> 00:17:59,040
in Social Dance class.

297
00:18:00,280 --> 00:18:02,800
I’ve held onto this grudge for over ten years.

298
00:18:02,800 --> 00:18:07,600
That someone like me, All-New, had to lose

299
00:18:07,600 --> 00:18:10,520
for the first and only time to someone like you,

300
00:18:10,520 --> 00:18:12,480
Onitsuka.

301
00:18:12,480 --> 00:18:14,080
Osaka!

302
00:18:14,080 --> 00:18:18,080
Yeah, whatever. Therefore, I challenge you...

303
00:18:19,080 --> 00:18:20,520
O-Liang-Suka.

304
00:18:20,520 --> 00:18:21,280
Osaka!

305
00:18:21,280 --> 00:18:22,280
Onitsuka.

306
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:23,160
I said Osaka!

307
00:18:23,160 --> 00:18:24,160
O-Liang-Saka.

308
00:18:24,160 --> 00:18:25,680
Osaka, damn it!

309
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:26,560
Yeah, that.

310
00:18:26,560 --> 00:18:27,720
I challenge you.

311
00:18:27,720 --> 00:18:29,720
Let’s settle this ballroom dance challenge on this plane once and for all.

312
00:18:32,160 --> 00:18:34,160
Challenge accepted.

313
00:18:39,440 --> 00:18:40,680
I must tell you,

314
00:18:40,680 --> 00:18:42,520
our Norwegian salmon sperm...

315
00:18:42,520 --> 00:18:45,480
Oh, my favorite concubine,

316
00:18:45,480 --> 00:18:46,960
you're back!

317
00:18:46,960 --> 00:18:49,680
Come here. We're going to do a demonstration.

318
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:52,040
Apply the sperm cream on your arm.

319
00:18:52,040 --> 00:18:53,120
Give me your arm.

320
00:18:53,120 --> 00:18:54,720
We're going to apply the sperm...

321
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:57,440
Salmon sperm!

322
00:18:57,440 --> 00:18:58,240
Yes.

323
00:18:58,240 --> 00:19:00,840
Now, let's try applying the sperm to the face.

324
00:19:00,840 --> 00:19:04,840
Doctor, let's call it the Norwegian salmon sperm.

325
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:07,040
And besides that, the sperm

326
00:19:07,040 --> 00:19:09,680
can also be applied to the collarbones.

327
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,800
This won't get us banned.

328
00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:12,960
Just rub it in like this.

329
00:19:12,960 --> 00:19:15,280
Oh, are you feeling...tingly?
What’s going on?

330
00:19:15,280 --> 00:19:17,480
Actually...

331
00:19:17,480 --> 00:19:20,800
I think I really need to tell you something, Doctor.

332
00:19:20,800 --> 00:19:23,920
I know you have special feelings for me.

333
00:19:23,920 --> 00:19:24,840
Huh?

334
00:19:24,840 --> 00:19:28,840
Just now, when you said I was cute and pointed at me.

335
00:19:28,960 --> 00:19:30,280
I mean you, Mr. Kreetha.

336
00:19:30,280 --> 00:19:31,000
Huh?

337
00:19:31,000 --> 00:19:34,080
Mr. Kreetha, you're cute.

338
00:19:34,080 --> 00:19:36,080
But I don't want to hurt your feelings, Doctor.

339
00:19:36,080 --> 00:19:37,480
Thank you for the good feelings,

340
00:19:37,480 --> 00:19:40,120
but we can still be friends.

341
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:43,400
What the hell is this?

342
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:45,640
Doctor, you don't have to lie or dodge the truth just to save face.

343
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,640
I don't mind.

344
00:19:46,640 --> 00:19:48,920
Are you crazy? What are you thinking?

345
00:19:48,920 --> 00:19:51,440
You think I like you?

346
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,120
Oh my god.

347
00:19:53,120 --> 00:19:54,520
Read my lips.

348
00:19:54,520 --> 00:19:55,960
Mr. Kreetha.

349
00:19:55,960 --> 00:19:58,960
I don't have feelings for you.

350
00:19:58,960 --> 00:20:00,760
The person I like is M...

351
00:20:00,760 --> 00:20:01,680
Me!

352
00:20:01,680 --> 00:20:02,640
No.

353
00:20:02,640 --> 00:20:04,400
The person I like is M...

354
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:05,240
Me!

355
00:20:05,240 --> 00:20:08,640
Argh! No! No!

356
00:20:08,640 --> 00:20:10,040
Ah!

357
00:20:10,040 --> 00:20:11,040
Chaba!

358
00:20:11,480 --> 00:20:12,480
Chaba!

359
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:13,880
Chaba!

360
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:17,160
Chaba!

361
00:20:18,040 --> 00:20:19,040
Chaba!

362
00:20:19,040 --> 00:20:20,880
Chaba, what's wrong, Chaba?

363
00:20:20,880 --> 00:20:21,880
Chaba!

364
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:24,560
Ms. Chaba!

365
00:20:24,560 --> 00:20:26,680
Ms. Chaba's internal elements are in total chaos.

366
00:20:26,680 --> 00:20:28,480
To faint like this,

367
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:30,440
she must have encountered something shocking.

368
00:20:30,440 --> 00:20:32,080
Oh, Chaba.

369
00:20:32,080 --> 00:20:36,080
Even if we couldn't sell anything on the livestream,
you didn't have to go into shock.

370
00:20:37,040 --> 00:20:37,400
What?

371
00:20:37,400 --> 00:20:39,120
Doctor.

372
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,200
Hey!

373
00:20:40,960 --> 00:20:43,760
She made 200,000 from selling second-hand stewed pork?

374
00:20:43,760 --> 00:20:44,720
No.

375
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:46,320
Hey!

376
00:20:46,320 --> 00:20:50,280
I'm selling Little Rocks.

377
00:20:50,280 --> 00:20:52,920
You sold rocks and made 200,000?

378
00:20:52,920 --> 00:20:53,560
Watch your mouth!

379
00:20:53,560 --> 00:20:54,200
Why?

380
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:56,040
Don't underestimate the power of the earth.

381
00:20:56,040 --> 00:21:01,080
These are Little Rocks, they're cute and lovable.

382
00:21:01,080 --> 00:21:03,200
Only 99 Baht each.

383
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:05,440
Raise them just to waste your money for fun.

384
00:21:05,440 --> 00:21:06,840
Ah...

385
00:21:06,840 --> 00:21:09,600
Kree, go find some snacks for the kids to eat.

386
00:21:09,600 --> 00:21:10,160
Huh?

387
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:13,160
Go! Get some snacks for Little Rocks.

388
00:21:13,160 --> 00:21:16,120
Little Rocks! Oh, you're so still.

389
00:21:16,120 --> 00:21:19,440
You don't eat and you don't talk.

390
00:21:19,440 --> 00:21:22,040
Everyone, watch Little Rocks eat some snacks.

391
00:21:22,040 --> 00:21:23,080
Oh, so they’ve already eaten it?

392
00:21:23,080 --> 00:21:27,080
Yes, they're eating right now.
So talented! Round of applause!

393
00:21:28,920 --> 00:21:31,640
Oh, people are commenting.

394
00:21:31,640 --> 00:21:33,240
Transferred for three rocks already.

395
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:36,360
Oh, someone already paid for three! Thank you!

396
00:21:36,360 --> 00:21:39,080
The one on the left is a bit cuter than the one on the right, isn't it?

397
00:21:39,080 --> 00:21:40,880
Actually, they are equally cute.

398
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:44,120
Don't say that, you'll hurt their feelings.

399
00:21:44,120 --> 00:21:47,240
Doctor, what do you call Chaba's condition in medical terms?

400
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:50,520
Medically, this behavior is considered abnormal.

401
00:21:50,520 --> 00:21:53,600
But in business, it's considered a genius.

402
00:21:53,600 --> 00:21:56,120
Genius?

403
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:56,920
Kree!

404
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,640
What?

405
00:21:58,640 --> 00:22:00,040
A businessman from Shanghai!

406
00:22:00,040 --> 00:22:02,480
He ordered 10,000 Little Rocks...

407
00:22:02,480 --> 00:22:05,160
to decorate a garden for Feng Shui.

408
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:06,080
It’s on!

409
00:22:06,080 --> 00:22:07,280
What's on?

410
00:22:07,280 --> 00:22:10,120
1,000,000 Baht!

411
00:22:10,120 --> 00:22:12,360
1,000,000 Baht is here!

412
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:14,720
1,000,000!

413
00:22:14,720 --> 00:22:15,560
1,000,000 Baht is here!

414
00:22:15,560 --> 00:22:18,040
1,000,000!

415
00:22:19,120 --> 00:22:20,160
Ms. Chaba.

416
00:22:20,160 --> 00:22:22,480
We aren't close enough for this kind hug!

417
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,280
Let me go! Ms. Chaba, let me go!

418
00:22:24,280 --> 00:22:27,600
Let go of me! Let go!

419
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:29,000
Alright.

420
00:22:29,000 --> 00:22:29,720
Oh?

421
00:22:29,720 --> 00:22:31,440
Kree, we're rich!

422
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:35,440
Yes, Chaba! 1,000,000 Baht!

423
00:22:38,120 --> 00:22:38,960
Ms. Chaba.

424
00:22:38,960 --> 00:22:39,560
Yes?

425
00:22:39,560 --> 00:22:41,040
Please, become my partner.

426
00:22:41,040 --> 00:22:42,120
What kind of partner?

427
00:22:42,120 --> 00:22:44,640
A life partner?

428
00:22:44,640 --> 00:22:45,560
How cringy!

429
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,760
I'm asking you to be my business partner.

430
00:22:47,760 --> 00:22:48,840
Because I...

431
00:22:48,840 --> 00:22:51,600
see your potential.

432
00:22:51,600 --> 00:22:52,840
Even with an ordinary rock,

433
00:22:52,840 --> 00:22:53,880
you could give it such value.

434
00:22:53,880 --> 00:22:54,280
Little Rocks...

435
00:22:54,680 --> 00:22:55,080
Little Rocks...

436
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:58,680
Even with Little Rocks, you could create such value.

437
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:00,680
So, what more could you do with my sperm?

438
00:23:00,680 --> 00:23:01,360
Huh?

439
00:23:01,360 --> 00:23:03,520
My Norwegian salmon sperm.

440
00:23:03,520 --> 00:23:05,520
Please consider my offer.

441
00:23:26,880 --> 00:23:28,960
My pinky toe has a cramp.

442
00:23:28,960 --> 00:23:30,200
Get up, New!

443
00:23:30,200 --> 00:23:32,520
You can’t let the grudge you’ve been holding for years

444
00:23:32,520 --> 00:23:34,200
end just because of a pinky toe cramp.

445
00:23:34,200 --> 00:23:35,200
Let me go.

446
00:23:43,400 --> 00:23:47,400
Honestly, I’ve never met anyone who matches my rhythm as well as you do.

447
00:23:48,280 --> 00:23:50,760
Me neither.

448
00:24:00,640 --> 00:24:03,640
Wait, how did this suddenly turn into a BL series?

449
00:24:06,480 --> 00:24:08,760
Sky, Sky!

450
00:24:08,760 --> 00:24:10,240
Are you possessed?

451
00:24:10,240 --> 00:24:13,840
Possessed by what?
My shipper brain is working hard.

452
00:24:13,840 --> 00:24:17,160
I could die happy right now.

453
00:24:17,160 --> 00:24:18,640
Scream! Scream for it!

454
00:24:18,640 --> 00:24:20,640
Everyone, stop!

455
00:24:27,480 --> 00:24:30,000
Do you have any idea who you're raising your voice at?

456
00:24:30,000 --> 00:24:32,640
That is the Purser of this flight!

457
00:24:32,640 --> 00:24:34,920
How could you raise your voice at her like that?

458
00:24:34,920 --> 00:24:37,400
Raise your voice at me instead!

459
00:24:38,240 --> 00:24:44,240
Scream! Scream it out! Oh my god, this is crazy!
He’s so freaking handsome!

460
00:24:44,400 --> 00:24:48,080
I have to thank you, Ms. Petch.

461
00:24:48,080 --> 00:24:52,080
Because of the clumsiness of your crew, Auntie...

462
00:24:52,760 --> 00:24:55,960
I’ve come up with the choreography for our new single.

463
00:24:55,960 --> 00:24:56,960
Voyage!

464
00:25:07,400 --> 00:25:10,400
Hold it, Petchgam Ploy. Pull yourself together.

465
00:25:14,160 --> 00:25:15,960
Is Ms. Petchgam Ploy okay?

466
00:25:15,960 --> 00:25:19,400
Or is she processing how many points to deduct from us?

467
00:25:19,400 --> 00:25:22,400
Or maybe she just needs to poop?
Should we have Sky stand in for her?

468
00:25:30,320 --> 00:25:32,120
Oh, but this is Paris...

469
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:33,960
Oh, I can't take it.

470
00:25:33,960 --> 00:25:35,400
Oh, this is too much.

471
00:25:35,400 --> 00:25:36,400
This is way too close.

472
00:25:44,880 --> 00:25:47,280
Auntie? Auntie?

473
00:25:47,280 --> 00:25:47,960
Auntie, are you okay?

474
00:25:47,960 --> 00:25:49,200
Ms. Petch is dead!

475
00:25:49,200 --> 00:25:51,840
Call an ambulance, quick! Call the rescue squad!

476
00:25:51,840 --> 00:25:53,560
The rescue squad! Ms. Petch is dead!

477
00:25:53,560 --> 00:25:55,560
We're in the air, you idiot!

478
00:26:10,520 --> 00:26:13,760
Has Paris landed in my heart yet?

479
00:26:13,760 --> 00:26:15,760
We've landed at the airport an hour ago, ma'am.

480
00:26:17,400 --> 00:26:20,720
Oh! Why are you all crowding around me?

481
00:26:20,720 --> 00:26:22,400
Don't crowd me, and don't worry about me.

482
00:26:22,400 --> 00:26:24,280
I think you should worry about

483
00:26:24,280 --> 00:26:26,240
your own dimming career prospects instead.

484
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:29,120
But we really are worried about you, Ms. Petchgam Ploy.

485
00:26:29,120 --> 00:26:31,120
I’ve already called for an ambulance to be on standby

486
00:26:31,120 --> 00:26:34,680
just in case you want to get your heart checked, Ms. Petch.

487
00:26:34,680 --> 00:26:36,480
No need. I’m fine.

488
00:26:36,480 --> 00:26:41,080
Oh, how could you be fine, Ms. Petchgam Ploy?

489
00:26:41,560 --> 00:26:44,200
The reason you fainted

490
00:26:44,200 --> 00:26:46,240
was because...

491
00:26:46,240 --> 00:26:50,240
The winner of this test is Ms. Sky.

492
00:26:52,960 --> 00:26:56,880
What I was going to say is that Ms. Petchgam Ploy fainted

493
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,840
because she’s wearing an outfit so tight it's crushing her waist.

494
00:26:59,840 --> 00:27:01,800
The blood couldn't reach her brain,

495
00:27:01,800 --> 00:27:04,160
so she passed out.

496
00:27:04,160 --> 00:27:07,960
Oh, I thought she was just smitten by the Voyage boys.

497
00:27:07,960 --> 00:27:10,920
Huh? That's not it.

498
00:27:10,920 --> 00:27:13,800
Wait, I haven't said a word to anyone.

499
00:27:13,800 --> 00:27:15,680
If you didn't say anything, how would they know?

500
00:27:15,680 --> 00:27:17,080
I don't know.

501
00:27:17,080 --> 00:27:19,720
Honestly, it was pretty obvious, Ms. Petch.

502
00:27:19,720 --> 00:27:21,320
Yes, indeed.

503
00:27:21,320 --> 00:27:24,080
According to the principles of statistics and human behavior,

504
00:27:24,080 --> 00:27:25,800
Ms. Petchgam Ploy's pupils

505
00:27:25,800 --> 00:27:29,480
dilate by 0.5 mm every time Paris gets close.

506
00:27:29,480 --> 00:27:31,200
In short, you're a fangirl.

507
00:27:31,200 --> 00:27:34,880
Was it really that obvious?

508
00:27:34,880 --> 00:27:37,040
But you don't have to worry, Ms. Petch.

509
00:27:37,040 --> 00:27:40,800
I think you're actually quite cute when you're like that.

510
00:27:40,800 --> 00:27:43,000
It makes us feel less tense around you, right?

511
00:27:43,000 --> 00:27:45,960
Exactly. You look more human, more approachable.

512
00:27:45,960 --> 00:27:47,600
But I am human!

513
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:51,600
Really, huh? You're so full of yourself!

514
00:27:53,040 --> 00:27:56,360
All right, then. For this week's Weakest Link...

515
00:27:56,360 --> 00:27:58,920
the loser of this test is...

516
00:27:58,920 --> 00:28:00,920
Ms. Sky.

517
00:28:04,240 --> 00:28:06,080
Why me?

518
00:28:06,080 --> 00:28:07,840
I was just winning a moment ago!

519
00:28:07,840 --> 00:28:09,680
Because you told my secret to everyone else.

520
00:28:09,680 --> 00:28:10,760
You blackmailed me.

521
00:28:10,760 --> 00:28:13,920
I’m deducting a full one hundred points!

522
00:28:13,920 --> 00:28:15,840
You can't do that, Ms. Petchgam Ploy!

523
00:28:15,840 --> 00:28:17,760
Please don't do this to me.

524
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:20,440
Forgive me, I was wrong!

525
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,680
Do you have anything to trade?

526
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:25,680
Yes! You can have this photo card of Paris.

527
00:28:29,120 --> 00:28:29,800
Down to eighty.

528
00:28:33,520 --> 00:28:36,280
Thank you so much, Little Rock.

529
00:28:36,280 --> 00:28:38,880
Thanks...

530
00:28:38,880 --> 00:28:41,320
Chaba!

531
00:28:41,320 --> 00:28:44,120
Why did you call us here so early? What’s up?

532
00:28:44,120 --> 00:28:46,640
I’ve figured it out.

533
00:28:46,640 --> 00:28:49,800
I’m going to change my destiny.

534
00:28:49,800 --> 00:28:52,480
What, you're changing your flight schedule again?

535
00:28:52,480 --> 00:28:53,480
No.

536
00:28:55,720 --> 00:28:57,960
I’m going to resign from being a flight attendant.

537
00:28:57,960 --> 00:28:58,680
Huh?

538
00:28:58,680 --> 00:28:59,680
What?

539
00:29:00,880 --> 00:29:04,680
Just as a bird that loves freedom shall not stay in a golden cage,

540
00:29:04,680 --> 00:29:09,520
a billionaire shall not serve water to passengers on a plane.

541
00:29:17,400 --> 00:29:18,440
Isn't she being a bit too dramatic?

542
00:29:18,440 --> 00:29:23,120
Oops, I forgot! I have an appointment with my SA.

543
00:29:23,120 --> 00:29:27,120
